decks.notes: This deck focuses on using aggressive Elemental creatures to quickly deal damage to the opponent. The key strategy revolves around generating card advantage with Keruga, the Macrosage as the companion, allowing you to draw extra cards. The deck also includes versatile instant spells like Dead / Gone and Fire / Ice to control the opponent's board and protect your creatures. Leyline Binding helps to lock down the opponent's key threats. Teferi, Time Raveler disrupts the opponent's strategy and provides additional card advantage. Overall, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with a strong board presence and efficient spell choices.

The deck focuses on using Indomitable Creativity to exchange Leyline Binding and Fable of the Mirror-Breaker for powerful creatures such as Archon of Cruelty. It also utilizes Wrenn and Six and Teferi, Time Raveler to control the board and disrupt the opponent's strategy. Lightning Bolt and Prismatic Ending provide removal options, while Spell Pierce and Prismari Command offer counterplay and flexibility. The triomes and fetchlands ensure consistent mana fixing, while Xander's Lounge provides a card draw engine. Overall, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with unexpected and game-changing creature exchanges while maintaining control.

The key concept of this Boros Aggro deck is to apply aggressive pressure on the opponent by utilizing efficient creatures and spells. The deck aims to control the board with removal spells like Prismatic Ending and Lightning Bolt, while also disrupting the opponent's game plan with cards like Mana Tithe and Blood Moon. It capitalizes on powerful creatures such as Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer, Solitude, and Seasoned Pyromancer to deal damage and generate card advantage. The deck's plan is further bolstered by the inclusion of powerful companions, with Obosh, the Preypiercer providing additional damage output.

The deck focuses on using Indomitable Creativity as the key card to generate powerful combos and create game-winning board states. It utilizes a mix of creatures and spells that provide value when sacrificed or enter the battlefield, such as Archon of Cruelty and Atraxa, Grand Unifier. The deck also includes several removal spells like Lightning Bolt and Prismari Command to control the board and protect the combo. Leyline Binding is used to prevent opponents from casting noncreature spells. Teferi, Time Raveler provides disruption and card advantage, while Wrenn and Six allows for consistent land drops. The deck includes a variety of lands to ensure proper mana fixing and consistency.

This deck focuses on aggressive gameplay using creatures with high power and low mana cost. It incorporates a wide range of colors, allowing for versatility in its spell choices. The key concept is to quickly apply pressure on the opponent, utilizing cards like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Tarmogoyf. It also aims to control the board through cards like Territorial Kavu and Stubborn Denial. Additionally, it utilizes Tribal Flames and Leyline Binding to deal direct damage to the opponent. The inclusion of Jegantha, the Wellspring as a companion adds an extra layer of consistency to the deck.

The main concept of this deck is to control the game by consistently countering and removing threats, while also generating card advantage and mana advantage through Wilderness Reclamation. The deck utilizes versatile spells like Archmage's Charm and Counterspell to stop opponents' plays, and removal spells like Abrupt Decay and Fatal Push to deal with problematic creatures. It also has powerful card draw with Memory Deluge and Snapcaster Mage for additional flexibility. The inclusion of cards like Hullbreaker Horror and Endurance provides additional win conditions and disruption options.

This Jund aggro deck focuses on utilizing efficient creatures like Ragavan, Tarmogoyf, and Wrenn and Six to quickly apply pressure on the opponent. With a mix of disruption spells like Inquisition of Kozilek and Lightning Bolt, as well as removal options like Fatal Push and Terminate, this deck aims to control the board while steadily advancing its own game plan. The inclusion of Urza's Saga provides additional utility and card advantage, while the companion Jegantha, the Wellspring adds a unique twist to the deck's strategy.

This deck focuses on fast and aggressive plays using efficient creatures like Fervent Champion and Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer. It also includes powerful equipment like Sword of Fire and Ice and Batterskull to enhance combat abilities. The deck aims to disrupt opponents with cards like Fury and Blood Moon while still maintaining a strong board presence. Additionally, cards like Solitude and Ephemerate provide removal and protection options. The inclusion of Stoneforge Mystic enables tutoring for key equipment pieces. The deck has a mix of aggressive and disruptive elements to pressure opponents and secure victories quickly.

The main concept of this deck is to create a fast and aggressive playstyle using a combination of cheap threats and disruptive spells. The deck aims to control the opponent's game plan while simultaneously applying pressure through creatures like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer, Murktide Regent, and Dragon's Rage Channeler. It utilizes efficient spells like Lightning Bolt, Unholy Heat, and Counterspell to disrupt the opponent's strategy and protect its own threats. Additionally, the inclusion of Mishra's Bauble and Expressive Iteration helps maintain card advantage and selection. The deck also incorporates land disruption with the inclusion of Blood Moon.
